	<section id="recipe">
		<p>
			Dark-chocolate covered strawberry protein bars...
			sounds like Valentine's day at Godiva Chocolaterie,
			doesn't it? 
			Well, I can promise you it's even better &#8211;
			not only is this luxuriously delicious and
			decadent-looking treat completely clean and healthy,
			but it's so simple and easy to make yourself. 
			Four
			words: Best. Valentines. Day. Ever.
		</p>
		<table class="ingredients">
			<caption>Ingredients</caption>
			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th class="amount" colspan="2">amount</th>
					<th class="name">name</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="0.1875"></td>
				<td class="unit">scoop</td>
				<td class="name">
					<script>
					amazonlink('B00ARK704C',
						'Cellucor COR Performance Whey ' +
						'Protein, Strawberry Milkshake, ' +
						'2lbs');
					</script>,
					<span class="altor">or</span> 
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="alt amount" data-lilachop-amount="0.1875"></td>
				<td class="alt unit">scoop</td>
				<td class="alt name">
					any strawberry-flavoured protein powder
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="0.0625"></td>
				<td class="unit">cup</td>
				<td class="name">
					<script>
						amazonlink('B00474AL2M',
						'Blue Diamond Breeze '+
						'unsweetened vanilla almond milk');
					</script>,
					<span class="altor">or</span> 
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="alt amount" data-lilachop-amount="0.0625"></td>
				<td class="alt unit">cup</td>
				<td class="alt name">any vegan milk</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="0.75"></td>
				<td class="unit">tbsp</td>
				<td class="name">
					<script>
					amazonlink('B003XB3NNE',
						'Secret Raw Coconut Flour');
					</script>
				</td> 
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="0.25"></td>
				<td class="unit">tbsp</td>
				<td class="name">
					<script>
						amazonlink('B001EO5Q64',
						'Nutiva organic virgin coconut oil');
					</script>	
				</td>

			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="1.25"></td>
				<td class="unit">whole</td>
				<td class="name">fresh strawberries</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="0.75"></td>
				<td class="unit">squares</td>
				<td class="name">
					<a href="http://www.amazon.com/dp/B002RBOCZE/?tag=lich048-20" class="amazon">Lindt Excellence dark chocolate 90%</a>
				</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
		<div class="servings">
			Change servings: 
			<input id="servings" type="number" min="0" step="1"
				value="4"
				onchange="changeservings(this.value);" /> 
		</div>
		<p>
			This recipe was adapted from
			<a href="http://proteinpow.com/2014/07/strawberry-protein-bars.html">Proteinpow's Strawberry Protein Bars recipe</a> 
			by Anna Sward. This protein genius taught me that the
			best part about making your own protein bars is that
			they don't have all the artificial binding agents,
			fillers and preservatives that store-bought ones do. 
			So nutrition, without the crap.  
			What's not to love about home-made protein bars?  
		</p>
		<table id="steps">
			<caption>Steps</caption>
			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th class="amount" colspan="2">time</th>
					<th>instruction</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount"></td>
				<td class="unit"></td>
				<td>
					Put aside the dark chocolate and 2 of the
					strawberries for last.
				</td> 
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount"></td>
				<td class="unit"></td>
				<td> 
					Blend all other ingredients together in a
					hand-held speed blender or food-processor until smooth 
				</td> 
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount"></td>
				<td class="unit"></td>
				<td>
					Shape batter into 2 bars.
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount"></td>
				<td class="unit"></td>
				<td>
					Melt the dark chocolate in a bain-marie
					or microwave (careful not to let it
					burn!)	
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount"></td>
				<td class="unit"></td>
				<td>
					Cover the bars by rolling
					them around in the melted dark
					chocolate, and place on aluminium
					foil-lined tray.
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount"></td>
				<td class="unit"></td>
				<td>
					Cut the remaining 2 strawberries in
					half, and place 1 half the on top of each bar.
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount">&lt;10</td>
				<td class="unit">minutes</td>
				<td>
					Refrigerate for a few hours, then devour!
				</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
		<p>
			Just take them out of the fridge, wrap them up in
			tinfoil and there you have it &#8211; protein bar to go! 
			This recipe serves 4, and macros are per bar.
		</p>
		<p>
			<b>Recipe tip</b>: to make the recipe richer, use
			full-fat milk or coconut milk to bind
			the protein powder together.  
		</p>
